title: Huawei says its own operating system could be ready this year if it can't use Google or Microsoft
text: The CEO of Huawei's consumer business, said Huawei's own operating system could be ready for use in China by fall this year.

title: Elon Musk’s Boring Company lands $48.7M contract for underground “people mover” in Las Vegas
text: The Boring Company, Elon Musk’s tunneling and transportation startup, has landed a $48.7 million project to shuttle people in an underground Loop system around the Las Vegas Convention Center. This is the company’s first commercial contract.

title: Asia's richest man to challenge Amazon's Jeff Bezos in India
text: With Amazon and Walmart facing regulatory hurdles in India, Reliance's Mukesh Ambani is gearing up to launch an e-commerce platform.

title: Active managers are beating the market again and Goldman has a strategy to ride their coattails
text: Active managers are having a breakout year and Goldman Sachs has a way to mirror their strategy.

title: Huawei unwanted: Asian shops shun phone trade-ins on Google suspension worries
text: Mobile phone retailers in some Asian countries are refusing to accept Huawei devices for trade-ins, as more consumers look to offload their device on worries Google suspending business with the Chinese firm will disrupt services.

title: Commerzbank may tweak strategy after Deutsche Bank talks collapse
text: Commerzbank may tweak its strategy following the collapse of merger talks with its larger rival Deutsche Bank, the lender's chief said on Wednesday.
